B) Your VPN provider matching logic is likely not doing what you want

This line is suspicious:

query = query.ilike("org_pattern", org.substring(0, 50));


That’s searching the pattern column for the org string. It’ll rarely match.

✅ Better approach:

If ASN match exists: great.

Else load a small list of provider patterns and do matching in code:

const { data } = await serviceClient
  .from("vpn_providers")
  .select("provider_name, confidence, asn, org_pattern");

const hit = data?.find(r => org && r.org_pattern && org.toLowerCase().includes(r.org_pattern.toLowerCase()));


Also: treat “hosting ASN” vs “consumer ASN” separately.

